1
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,951
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

2
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:46,879
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

3
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,966
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:54,596
My punishment was long overdue…

5
00:00:58,267 --> 00:01:00,102
and I think it's finally time.

6
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:06,400
A friend of mine died because of me.

7
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:12,948
On an island.

8
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:19,871
I'm the one who sent Seonu out to sea.

9
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:41,226
I swore I'd never allow myself
a moment of happiness…

10
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:51,028
but I guess I got too greedy.

11
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:12,883
EPISODE 11
RECONCILIATION, HEALING, AND…

12
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:23,100
You all saw the news, right?
About how Dr. Do's on medication.

13
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:26,145
- Shut that mouth of yours.
- It's just, the meds he's on--

14
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:28,606
Hey, I told you to shut it.

15
00:02:28,607 --> 00:02:30,691
Name one person here who isn't on meds.

16
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:33,444
So stop yapping and making
such a big deal out of nothing.

17
00:02:33,445 --> 00:02:36,530
Jeez, why do you keep telling me
to shut it?

18
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:41,202
I was just trying to say
that someone must have ratted out Dr. Do.

19
00:02:41,203 --> 00:02:44,915
It's not like we're gonna
gossip behind his back.

20
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,333
We're all family here.

21
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:48,626
You worry too much.

22
00:02:48,627 --> 00:02:51,170
That's the part that bothers me a little.

23
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:55,299
- That kind of personal info is top secret.
- Of course.

24
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,635
So who could have snitched
to the county office?

25
00:02:57,636 --> 00:02:58,719
That's true.

26
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:02,598
Whoever it was must have held
a grudge against Dr. Do, you know?

27
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:06,018
Oh, my! Chugging soju this early?

28
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:08,312
Hey, Geumja, give me
a bowl of seafood ramyeon.

29
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:09,356
Seafood ramyeon? Okay.

30
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:13,735
So what are we talking about?

31
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,654
Were you talking about that doctor?

32
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:18,489
Damn, that one's a riot.

33
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:20,491
He's on medication.

34
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:23,035
So you think someone
being on medication's a riot?

35
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:26,414
It's a bit late,
but isn't it such a relief

36
00:03:26,415 --> 00:03:28,583
that such vital information
has come to light?

37
00:03:30,127 --> 00:03:34,339
So, were you the one who did it?

38
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:39,969
Did you ruin his future
because he kept meddling in your affairs?

39
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:42,972
Have you lost your marbles, old man?

40
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:44,724
What the hell are you talking about?

41
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,270
If you don't want that jaw of yours
to get dislocated again,

42
00:03:49,271 --> 00:03:51,189
you'd better tell me the truth.

43
00:03:52,107 --> 00:03:54,316
Were you the one who ratted him out?

44
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:57,403
"Rat him out"?
What do you mean, "rat him out"?

45
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:59,738
I'll knock your teeth out, damn it.

46
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:02,283
You want to go?

47
00:04:02,284 --> 00:04:04,243
Being old won't save you.

48
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,911
You little shit…

49
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,580
"You little shit."

50
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:10,125
I don't go easy on thugs either.

51
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:12,626
What? "Thug"?

52
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:15,296
- Say that again!
- Oh, no…

53
00:04:15,297 --> 00:04:18,049
I'm not holding back anymore!

54
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:22,344
I'm busy, so why don't all three of you
jump me all at once?

55
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:23,804
Come on.

56
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:27,768
Bring it!

57
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:42,615
But you said
you don't know how to do this.

58
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,116
What?

59
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:47,870
You said you don't know how to do this!

60
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:49,497
Oh, I don't know how to do this?

61
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:50,832
- Yes.
- That's right.

62
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:55,879
Unfortunately, the only doctor who knows
how to reset a jaw is currently suspended.

63
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:00,634
Wait.

64
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:13,271
Just so you know, I'm pretty bad at this.

65
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:31,080
Hey, take your meds.

66
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:32,874
That'll be 1,100 won.

67
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:39,422
Does the staff here hold a grudge
against me or something?

68
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:43,175
Are you really asking
because you don't know?

69
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:48,472
It's because you keep going around
spreading weird rumors!

70
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:49,890
"Weird rumors"?

71
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,519
What do you mean, "weird rumors"?

72
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:54,396
Damn it!

73
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:10,287
Where did it…

74
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:14,748
Here.

75
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:17,794
Here it is.

76
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:27,053
Oh, Dr. Do's not in right now.

77
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:33,184
Can we talk for a moment?

78
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:43,194
What's going to happen
to Jiui now?

79
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:47,198
Once he's removed from his post,
he'll be leaving this place,

80
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:51,911
and he'll be serving the rest of
his military service on active duty.

81
00:06:57,834 --> 00:06:59,753
I heard from Dr. Do

82
00:07:00,462 --> 00:07:02,505
that he lost a friend on an island.

83
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,926
And that he's receiving
the overdue punishment now.

84
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:13,558
But you know what?

85
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:17,062
I don't think he should be punished
for what happened.

86
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:19,397
He did nothing wrong, after all.

87
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:24,486
I can't let him hate himself
while he's being punished for it.

88
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,242
Well…

89
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,536
Ms. Yuk.

90
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:38,416
Please don't hold Jiui back.

91
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:40,710
What?

92
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:43,963
Don't break Jiui's heart anymore
with words like that.

93
00:07:48,218 --> 00:07:52,514
I was the one who told the county office
that Jiui was on medication.

94
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:54,182
What?

95
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,392
But why on earth would you--

96
00:07:56,393 --> 00:08:00,188
I thought you heard all about why
an island is hell for Jiui.

97
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:07,862
Jiui and I suffered for a long time.

98
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:14,577
People say you should
get over your pain, right?

99
00:08:17,956 --> 00:08:18,957
No.

100
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:23,336
The only way to treat unbearable pain
is to run away from it.

101
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:26,171
That's why Jiui wants to leave.

102
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,674
It's because he wants to live.

103
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:38,059
I'm here to ask you…

104
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,355
not to try and stop Jiui from leaving.

105
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:46,526
I'm begging you.

106
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:52,407
Do you really think…

107
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:58,329
leaving the island will help him recover?

108
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:11,885
He'll get better
once he leaves this place.

109
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:38,952
TRANSFER DIRECTIVE FOR DERELICTION OF DUTY
BY PUBLIC HEALTH DOCTOR

110
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:40,413
DO JIUI

111
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,424
Want to have a drink?

112
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:00,266
Are you really going to leave?

113
00:10:03,645 --> 00:10:06,564
I'm sorry for putting you through
so much trouble.

114
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:12,403
There's no need to apologize.
It just sounds a bit selfish. That's all.

115
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:22,247
I don't think PH docs should have to
take the fall for something like this.

116
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:40,515
PYEONDONG GODDESS

117
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:49,439
The number you have dialed
cannot be reached at this moment.

118
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,441
What the heck?

119
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,111
- Ms. Hwang.
- What is it?

120
00:10:54,112 --> 00:10:57,114
Did Ms. Jeongseon go somewhere?
I haven't seen her today.

121
00:10:57,115 --> 00:10:58,198
Lift your leg.

122
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:01,451
She used her monthly leave,
saying she had to go somewhere urgently.

123
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:04,663
Huh? Why did she use
a monthly leave all of a sudden?

124
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,081
Why are you asking me that?

125
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:08,375
You, of all people, should know what's up.

126
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,586
Did you get into
a lovers' quarrel or something?

127
00:11:10,587 --> 00:11:12,588
No, it's not like that.

128
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:16,008
Are you sure you're not
just unaware of it?

129
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:20,388
She did seem kind of down,
but are you suggesting that was a fight?

130
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,931
You really don't know?

131
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:26,644
You don't know
whether you got into a fight or not?

132
00:11:28,188 --> 00:11:31,774
Did we really get into a fight?

133
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:36,446
I swear she was happy, though.

134
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:40,449
How on earth did you get into
the College of Korean Medicine?

135
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:42,827
It's the darndest thing.

136
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,594
LOVELY NINNYHAMMER

137
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,354
LOVELY NINNYHAMMER

138
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,530
- Thank you.
-  Thank you.

139
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,408
- Take care.
- Okay.

140
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:40,509
Where are you, Ms. Eom?

141
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:42,845
Have I upset you by any chance?

142
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:50,560
- Ms. Eom Jeongseon.
- Yes.

143
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:53,063
Please come into the examination room.

144
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:54,065
Okay.

145
00:12:56,734 --> 00:13:00,363
Your blood test came back as 110,
which means you're definitely pregnant.

146
00:13:02,532 --> 00:13:04,033
I see.

147
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:09,913
So I really am pregnant.

148
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:11,291
I really am.

149
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:17,170
It's still early, so I'm not sure
we'll see a gestational sac,

150
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,548
but would you like to do an ultrasound?

151
00:13:19,549 --> 00:13:21,509
- No.
- Huh?

152
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:25,012
I don't want to do the ultrasound.

153
00:13:25,013 --> 00:13:27,056
I don't think I need it.

154
00:13:27,849 --> 00:13:29,350
I see.

155
00:13:30,977 --> 00:13:37,692
But my morning sickness has been
causing me some trouble, so…

156
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,029
I'll write you a prescription.

157
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,447
Please wait outside.

158
00:13:43,448 --> 00:13:44,449
Okay.

159
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:04,385
DAILECTIN

160
00:14:31,788 --> 00:14:34,916
He'll get better
once he leaves this place.

161
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:41,547
Ms. Yuk.

162
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:45,801
Ms. Yuk?

163
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:47,344
Oh, hey.

164
00:14:47,345 --> 00:14:50,389
What's on your mind?
I called you multiple times.

165
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,811
It's nothing.

166
00:14:59,482 --> 00:15:00,942
Are you okay?

167
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:07,615
I don't know.

168
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:45,736
I'm good.

169
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:50,950
I took it off because it's hot.

170
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:52,869
Right.

171
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:56,706
But since I took it off,
let me hang it on you for a bit.

172
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:08,551
Looking out into the sea
always brings me peace of mind.

173
00:16:12,847 --> 00:16:15,808
It's always there for me,
just the way I remember it.

174
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:23,440
No matter when I return,
or how I've changed,

175
00:16:23,441 --> 00:16:25,276
it's always right here.

176
00:16:30,573 --> 00:16:32,783
Even if everything else leaves me…

177
00:16:35,453 --> 00:16:37,872
the sea will always be here for me.

178
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,293
But I found out…

179
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,673
that this everlasting ocean…

180
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:57,558
was a source of never-ending pain
for someone else.

181
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:10,488
And that really…

182
00:17:18,663 --> 00:17:20,373
…breaks my heart.

183
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:44,521
Dr. Yong, what are you doing here?

184
00:17:44,522 --> 00:17:45,605
Ms. Eom!

185
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:47,232
Where on earth were you all day?

186
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,818
I couldn't reach you at all.

187
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,153
Did we have a fight?

188
00:17:51,946 --> 00:17:53,364
What are you talking about?

189
00:17:53,990 --> 00:17:55,240
Right?

190
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:57,033
So we didn't fight, right?

191
00:17:57,034 --> 00:18:00,370
Then why didn't you pick up the phone?

192
00:18:00,371 --> 00:18:02,831
I was kind of scared for a bit.

193
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:05,250
That's no reason to wait
in front of my house.

194
00:18:05,251 --> 00:18:07,460
It's cold outside.

195
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:11,507
Well, there was something
I wanted to discuss with you.

196
00:18:13,259 --> 00:18:14,844
Discuss with me?

197
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:21,725
This is nice.

198
00:18:21,726 --> 00:18:25,812
I'm actually dying to know
where you've been,

199
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:29,942
but healthy relationships need boundaries,
so I won't ask.

200
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,529
So what did you want to discuss with me?

201
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:36,324
Uh…

202
00:18:36,991 --> 00:18:37,992
Well…

203
00:18:39,744 --> 00:18:40,745
The thing is…

204
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:44,832
I have to apply for a transfer soon.

205
00:18:47,585 --> 00:18:49,837
Transfer, huh?

206
00:18:52,006 --> 00:18:53,882
I've thought it over,

207
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:57,970
and I think I should work
somewhere near my dad's hospital next.

208
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,432
What do you think?

209
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:05,853
I guess you should do that.

210
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:11,858
To be honest,
I was really conflicted since you're here,

211
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:15,820
but to start working at my dad's hospital
as soon as I'm done being a PH doc,

212
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:18,031
I'll need a lot of clinical experience,

213
00:19:18,032 --> 00:19:21,744
but the cases around here are all
pretty much the same, so…

214
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:26,289
By your dad's hospital,
are you talking about the one in Seoul?

215
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:28,668
Yes, on Baeng Baeng Intersection.

216
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:33,339
You're getting farther and farther away.

217
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:36,174
What?

218
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,759
It's nothing.

219
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:40,512
But why bother discussing that with me?

220
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:42,389
You should go if you have to go.

221
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:45,016
Of course, I should ask you.

222
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:47,811
This is a very important decision for us.

223
00:19:47,812 --> 00:19:50,522
Besides, we like each other,

224
00:19:50,523 --> 00:19:53,943
so we owe it to each other
to discuss important matters beforehand.

225
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:39,947
Oh, my…

226
00:20:43,284 --> 00:20:44,451
Gosh.

227
00:20:44,452 --> 00:20:48,830
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

228
00:20:48,831 --> 00:20:52,333
Yikes, you should really watch
where you're going.

229
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:53,752
- Are you okay?
-  Yeah.

230
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:55,920
I didn't see a frozen patch on the ground.

231
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:58,006
You should have been more careful.

232
00:20:58,007 --> 00:21:03,595
Being careful won't help you avoid
the inevitable in life.

233
00:21:03,596 --> 00:21:05,014
Yeah, you're right.

234
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:09,727
Ms. Eom, something on your mind recently?

235
00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:13,563
Something on my mind?

236
00:21:13,564 --> 00:21:14,647
Not at all.

237
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:15,775
Yeah, right.

238
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:19,611
You've been acting really strange.

239
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:24,240
You don't complain or pout
as much as you used to.

240
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,786
Something feels really off.

241
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,955
Nothing gets past you.

242
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:32,583
Well, what is it?

243
00:21:34,502 --> 00:21:40,173
It's just, I feel like I'm damned if I do
and damned if I don't,

244
00:21:40,174 --> 00:21:43,219
so I'm just trying to figure out
which way would hurt less.

245
00:21:44,178 --> 00:21:45,304
You're "damned"?

246
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:47,765
What do you mean you're "damned"?

247
00:21:50,226 --> 00:21:51,644
Huh?

248
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:55,689
What the…

249
00:21:56,524 --> 00:21:58,150
I guess it's a secret.

250
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:12,915
When every path seems
to lead you to a cliff

251
00:22:14,041 --> 00:22:17,461
and it feels like the whole world
is out to get you,

252
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:21,674
you just need to stick close
to the people who are on your side.

253
00:22:23,425 --> 00:22:25,469
It won't hurt as much when you fall.

254
00:22:26,637 --> 00:22:31,350
Having someone who can cry with you
will make it a little better.

255
00:22:34,562 --> 00:22:36,397
Is Dr. Jucheon not up to the task?

256
00:22:38,816 --> 00:22:41,277
It's not like that.

257
00:22:43,404 --> 00:22:44,947
Tell me if you ever need me.

258
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:47,700
You know I cry easily.

259
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:52,579
Having someone to cry with you
will make it a little better, okay?

260
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:54,456
We can pass the tissue around and all.

261
00:22:57,793 --> 00:22:58,836
Okay.

262
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:06,467
This too shall pass, okay?

263
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:08,761
This too shall pass.

264
00:23:08,762 --> 00:23:10,014
Goodness.

265
00:23:57,436 --> 00:23:58,646
Someone on my side?

266
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:17,039
What the…

267
00:24:26,507 --> 00:24:27,841
What was that…

268
00:24:29,301 --> 00:24:31,595
DON'T SKIP YOUR MEALS, DR. DO

269
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:36,433
FEELING DOWN?
HERE'S A PICK-ME-UP!

270
00:24:53,534 --> 00:24:56,412
Dr. Do,
can you help me with something?

271
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,334
Ta-da!

272
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:05,170
You're here.

273
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:08,841
I mean…

274
00:25:10,009 --> 00:25:11,176
What is all this?

275
00:25:11,885 --> 00:25:14,805
Let's make Christmas preparations
for our clinic together.

276
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:26,649
Come on, is that the best you can do?

277
00:25:26,650 --> 00:25:28,152
It's too high up.

278
00:25:28,777 --> 00:25:30,528
I got it.

279
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:32,197
- I got it.
- You got it.

280
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:37,827
Does the clinic always set up
a Christmas tree like this every year?

281
00:25:37,828 --> 00:25:40,414
I wouldn't know.
This is my first Christmas here too.

282
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:43,082
Ah.

283
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:45,961
I just wanted to see you
and needed a good excuse,

284
00:25:46,712 --> 00:25:48,839
so this is what I came up with.

285
00:25:53,343 --> 00:25:55,012
It seemed like a solid excuse

286
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,515
to trick my awkward boyfriend
into coming down.

287
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:06,899
I'm sorry.

288
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:12,279
Don't be.

289
00:26:13,197 --> 00:26:14,865
I'm the one who should be apologizing.

290
00:26:19,912 --> 00:26:24,958
I had no idea what you were going through,
but I clung to you anyway.

291
00:26:30,339 --> 00:26:32,633
I was the one who said
you should cross the ocean,

292
00:26:33,425 --> 00:26:35,594
and I'm the one who begged you to return.

293
00:26:38,388 --> 00:26:41,767
You must have struggled so much here,
surrounded on all sides by the ocean.

294
00:26:47,189 --> 00:26:48,899
Surrounded or not,

295
00:26:50,651 --> 00:26:53,320
I wanted to hang in there
because I had you, Ms. Yuk. But…

296
00:26:58,742 --> 00:27:00,035
I'm sorry.

297
00:27:07,251 --> 00:27:09,753
Looks like we just keep having to
apologize to each other.

298
00:27:21,431 --> 00:27:24,935
I had a million lines to say
to get you to stay…

299
00:27:26,979 --> 00:27:29,231
but seeing you now,
I don't think I should.

300
00:27:32,985 --> 00:27:34,236
Can you just…

301
00:27:39,241 --> 00:27:41,827
promise me one thing?

302
00:27:49,543 --> 00:27:52,087
That promise you made to yourself
to never be happy again.

303
00:27:55,424 --> 00:27:56,884
Don't keep it.

304
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:03,974
I really want to hold on to you so much,

305
00:28:04,975 --> 00:28:07,561
but the reason I'm not doing so…

306
00:28:14,568 --> 00:28:17,029
is because I want you to be happy.

307
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:45,056
Come on.

308
00:28:45,057 --> 00:28:47,768
You weren't very good in art class
when you were a kid, right?

309
00:28:49,895 --> 00:28:52,605
Hey, I was even in an art club
back in elementary school.

310
00:28:52,606 --> 00:28:54,441
My teacher said I was really good at art.

311
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:56,568
Who was your teacher?

312
00:28:57,277 --> 00:29:00,364
They really filled your head
with lies, huh?

313
00:29:06,954 --> 00:29:08,204
Ms. Hwang.

314
00:29:08,205 --> 00:29:09,622
What's all this?

315
00:29:09,623 --> 00:29:11,791
It's Christmas,
so we wanted to liven things up.

316
00:29:11,792 --> 00:29:14,961
It sure is nice to work with
such young coworkers.

317
00:29:14,962 --> 00:29:17,089
Wow, it looks like
a department store in here.

318
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:19,883
Gosh, it's so pretty.

319
00:29:21,051 --> 00:29:22,427
So pretty.

320
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:26,807
I left something here,
so I'm just here to get it.

321
00:29:29,810 --> 00:29:33,146
Oh, that hurts.

322
00:29:45,283 --> 00:29:46,994
Jeez, I don't see it anywhere.

323
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:49,997
Goodness.

324
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:56,712
Goodness me.

325
00:29:58,005 --> 00:30:00,132
Where could I have put it?

326
00:30:01,383 --> 00:30:02,550
Is everything all right?

327
00:30:02,551 --> 00:30:03,552
It's nothing.

328
00:30:04,177 --> 00:30:05,594
Now, where could it be?

329
00:30:05,595 --> 00:30:08,681
It's nothing? You can't even see
what's right in front of you.

330
00:30:08,682 --> 00:30:10,933
Hey, I told you it's nothing.

331
00:30:10,934 --> 00:30:14,896
- Take a seat here for a moment.
- I told you I'm okay.

332
00:30:16,523 --> 00:30:17,691
Seriously.

333
00:30:26,867 --> 00:30:29,076
I think you should go
to the hospital right now.

334
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:31,829
Hey, I'm okay.
There's nothing to worry about.

335
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:33,330
I'm not a patient or anything.

336
00:30:33,331 --> 00:30:35,332
Or I could introduce you to a doctor--

337
00:30:35,333 --> 00:30:38,587
I told you to leave me alone!
I'll take care of it myself!

338
00:30:41,173 --> 00:30:44,092
Ms. Hwang, why…

339
00:30:46,970 --> 00:30:47,971
Oh…

340
00:30:52,642 --> 00:30:55,145
I just need to wait it out
a little longer.

341
00:30:55,812 --> 00:31:01,901
Something felt off about my eyes
a few months ago, so I got insurance.

342
00:31:01,902 --> 00:31:04,528
But I was told that
I'd have to wait another three months

343
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,823
before they could cover my condition.

344
00:31:12,412 --> 00:31:17,292
It's pretty ironic that a nurse is trying
to ignore her own illness, right?

345
00:31:18,043 --> 00:31:19,710
But what can I do?

346
00:31:19,711 --> 00:31:22,714
Life will go on even after
I'm done treating my sickness.

347
00:31:23,799 --> 00:31:28,887
If we go bankrupt because I'm sick,
how will we pay for our son's education?

348
00:31:29,554 --> 00:31:32,432
Our eldest son's a very smart boy

349
00:31:33,266 --> 00:31:37,145
and he said his dream is
to study overseas in the States.

350
00:31:40,607 --> 00:31:41,691
He's got a dream, okay?

351
00:31:44,236 --> 00:31:47,948
What kind of mother would I be
if I got in the way of his dreams?

352
00:31:52,077 --> 00:31:56,080
Things were better when I was young enough
to only worry about whatever ailed me.

353
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:58,666
Now, the sickness doesn't scare me.

354
00:31:58,667 --> 00:32:00,293
The bills do.

355
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:11,596
Life can be really unfair.

356
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:14,266
So unfair.

357
00:32:19,104 --> 00:32:21,857
I wasn't done making dinner,
so I should hurry back.

358
00:32:24,734 --> 00:32:26,903
Thank you.

359
00:32:52,179 --> 00:32:54,472
I came across people like her
a lot in the ER.

360
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:58,059
People who hide their condition,

361
00:32:58,894 --> 00:33:01,479
not because they're scared of it,
but because of the costs.

362
00:33:05,192 --> 00:33:10,530
Whether it's then or now,
there's still nothing I can do for her.

363
00:33:24,169 --> 00:33:25,754
Just a sec.

364
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:33,802
- Hello?
-  Hey, Hari.

365
00:33:33,803 --> 00:33:36,014
You need to come right now.

366
00:33:36,932 --> 00:33:41,143
LUCKY SUPERMARKET

367
00:33:41,144 --> 00:33:42,228
What is it, Granny?

368
00:33:42,229 --> 00:33:44,230
This man came into the supermarket…

369
00:33:44,231 --> 00:33:47,358
…looking for painkillers
and then just collapsed.

370
00:33:47,359 --> 00:33:49,318
He's sweating bullets

371
00:33:49,319 --> 00:33:52,112
and shaking like a leaf.

372
00:33:52,113 --> 00:33:57,117
I told him we should go to the center,
but he was vehemently against that.

373
00:33:57,118 --> 00:33:58,119
Goodness.

374
00:34:04,167 --> 00:34:05,585
Are you okay, sir?

375
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:12,591
I'll try pressing you
like I did back then.

376
00:34:21,351 --> 00:34:22,435
Dr. Do.

377
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:28,108
- It's the same symptoms as before.
- Should I call a chopper?

378
00:34:29,276 --> 00:34:31,860
The painkillers made the pain go away,

379
00:34:31,861 --> 00:34:35,490
and the folks at the hospital
said the scans came out clean.

380
00:34:37,158 --> 00:34:41,870
I already feel terrible
for causing the death of that pilot

381
00:34:41,871 --> 00:34:45,500
and damaging your reputation.

382
00:34:48,503 --> 00:34:50,129
I'm just going to go now.

383
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:53,799
- Sir.
- Dr. Do.

384
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,342
We should get him to a hospital.

385
00:34:55,343 --> 00:34:56,553
Okay.

386
00:34:57,804 --> 00:34:59,347
Hang in there, sir.

387
00:35:00,265 --> 00:35:02,517
No, you can't…

388
00:35:08,982 --> 00:35:11,442
- Yeopoong-gun operations center.
- This is Pyeondongdo.

389
00:35:11,443 --> 00:35:14,236
We have a suspected appendicitis
needing immediate transfer.

390
00:35:14,237 --> 00:35:16,405
Isn't that
where that accident happened?

391
00:35:16,406 --> 00:35:18,824
We can't dispatch anyone
under current emergency protocols.

392
00:35:18,825 --> 00:35:21,785
What's that got to do with this?
There's a patient here.

393
00:35:21,786 --> 00:35:23,746
Well, the sea fog is too thick,

394
00:35:23,747 --> 00:35:25,789
and we don't have any choppers on standby.

395
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:27,416
A man is dying right now!

396
00:35:27,417 --> 00:35:30,377
I'm sorry, but due to protocol,
we can't offer you any assistance.

397
00:35:30,378 --> 00:35:31,379
- I'm sorry.
- Hey--

398
00:35:32,255 --> 00:35:33,465
Hello?

399
00:35:38,428 --> 00:35:40,847
Hey, do you have a minute?

400
00:35:41,514 --> 00:35:44,434
We could use your help here.

401
00:35:45,769 --> 00:35:47,771
Careful. Take it slow…

402
00:35:49,648 --> 00:35:51,440
Won't it be dangerous, Mr. Park?

403
00:35:51,441 --> 00:35:53,942
We can't let a man die
because it's a little dangerous,

404
00:35:53,943 --> 00:35:55,361
not after I lived like that!

405
00:35:55,362 --> 00:35:58,073
If you say he needs to go,
we're getting him there!

406
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,491
I'm sorry.

407
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:02,409
Hey, don't say that.

408
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:04,995
Why would you feel sorry
for wanting to live?

409
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:06,581
You just hang in there, okay?

410
00:36:08,458 --> 00:36:09,626
Jiui.

411
00:36:11,127 --> 00:36:12,544
Think it over.

412
00:36:12,545 --> 00:36:14,254
You're on probation.
If something goes wrong,

413
00:36:14,255 --> 00:36:17,132
you might actually have to
step down as a doctor for good.

414
00:36:17,133 --> 00:36:18,760
Let's wait it out a little longer.

415
00:36:21,763 --> 00:36:23,932
What if he were to lose his life?

416
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:28,353
We'd be powerless to do anything,
just like back then.

417
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:38,737
- Let's go, Mr. Park.
- Okay.

418
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:41,491
Hold on tight, folks.
The winter winds are brutal!

419
00:36:44,119 --> 00:36:45,453
Let me help you put one on.

420
00:37:02,971 --> 00:37:04,888
Please take good care of him.

421
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:06,473
Save him! That's all we ask!

422
00:37:06,474 --> 00:37:12,855
Oh, mighty Dragon King,
please grant our people safe passage.

423
00:37:12,856 --> 00:37:13,939
Goodness…

424
00:37:30,039 --> 00:37:32,499
This is a patient
previously transferred for R/O appy.

425
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:34,877
He now has
localized RLQ tenderness and rebound.

426
00:37:34,878 --> 00:37:36,670
He's running a temp of 37.7

427
00:37:36,671 --> 00:37:38,506
- and experiencing chills.
- Got it.

428
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:46,472
EMERGENCY DISPATCH

429
00:38:07,869 --> 00:38:10,205
Dr. Do, here.

430
00:38:10,872 --> 00:38:12,372
Have a sip while it's hot.

431
00:38:12,373 --> 00:38:15,126
Thank you.

432
00:38:17,879 --> 00:38:20,839
Damn, that really
hits the spot.

433
00:38:26,679 --> 00:38:28,807
By the way, Dr. Do…

434
00:38:30,099 --> 00:38:31,601
Are you really leaving?

435
00:38:34,646 --> 00:38:37,607
Come on.
Why not fight for yourself a bit longer?

436
00:38:39,818 --> 00:38:41,653
Would that be too much to ask of you?

437
00:38:45,615 --> 00:38:46,866
I'm sorry.

438
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:51,287
What's causing you so much pain?

439
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:58,461
When I heard you were on medication,
hearing that really broke my heart.

440
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:05,384
You risked your life many times to save us
while taking medication yourself,

441
00:39:05,385 --> 00:39:08,596
so sending you off like this
without protecting you…

442
00:39:09,848 --> 00:39:12,392
It just doesn't feel right.

443
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:20,525
At times like this,
living on an island feels like a crime.

444
00:39:21,276 --> 00:39:22,694
It truly does…

445
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:27,657
Dr. Do!

446
00:39:30,577 --> 00:39:33,579
They just started operating
on the patient for appendicitis.

447
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:37,249
It went unnoticed last time
because the appendix was obscured,

448
00:39:37,250 --> 00:39:39,127
but he's just gone into emergency surgery.

449
00:39:41,546 --> 00:39:44,215
They said it was a really close call.

450
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:49,219
You saved this patient's life, Dr. Do.

451
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:53,307
Wow. So he made it, huh?

452
00:39:53,308 --> 00:39:55,226
He made it.

453
00:39:58,730 --> 00:40:00,231
Goodness.

454
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:15,121
What's on your mind?

455
00:40:19,584 --> 00:40:21,669
That appendicitis patient.

456
00:40:23,254 --> 00:40:25,423
He apologized to me.

457
00:40:27,634 --> 00:40:31,846
Despite the pain and fear of death.

458
00:40:33,806 --> 00:40:36,850
Treatments that would be considered
trivial on the mainland

459
00:40:36,851 --> 00:40:39,312
aren't very accessible on an island.

460
00:40:40,772 --> 00:40:43,649
That's why people end up
losing their lives…

461
00:40:43,650 --> 00:40:47,195
…over some stupid lights or appendicitis.

462
00:40:50,156 --> 00:40:54,953
To save someone's life,
one must put their own life on the line.

463
00:40:58,289 --> 00:41:00,958
I guess that's why
islanders here apologize

464
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:04,170
before begging the doctor
to save their lives.

465
00:41:06,965 --> 00:41:09,842
Because they're afraid
someone might get hurt because of them.

466
00:41:13,429 --> 00:41:15,139
But that's unacceptable.

467
00:41:17,266 --> 00:41:18,558
Hmm.

468
00:41:18,559 --> 00:41:20,228
I mean, wanting to live shouldn't be…

469
00:41:21,896 --> 00:41:23,982
something you have to apologize for.

470
00:41:31,990 --> 00:41:37,787
-  All right, let's go!
-  Okay. Let's get up.

471
00:41:44,002 --> 00:41:45,461
You two go on without me.

472
00:41:46,462 --> 00:41:48,130
- What?
-  Huh?

473
00:41:48,131 --> 00:41:49,173
Dr. Do!

474
00:41:50,883 --> 00:41:52,635
Huh?

475
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:01,351
2025-2026 YEOPOONG-GUN

476
00:42:01,352 --> 00:42:03,187
EMERGENCY MEDICAL CARE
MODERNIZATION PLAN

477
00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:07,399
Handle things quietly from now on

478
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:10,945
if you want to keep your job
as director, got it?

479
00:42:12,780 --> 00:42:13,781
Yes, sir.

480
00:42:15,992 --> 00:42:18,035
You can't just
barge in here like this.

481
00:42:18,036 --> 00:42:19,119
I said you can't!

482
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,495
What the hell?

483
00:42:22,874 --> 00:42:25,834
It'll be in your best interest
to talk to me right now.

484
00:42:25,835 --> 00:42:27,919
Otherwise, I might just take these files

485
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,423
straight to those reporters
that you like so much.

486
00:42:32,717 --> 00:42:34,093
Leave us.

487
00:42:43,895 --> 00:42:48,190
I can't accept your decision
to remove me from my PH doc post.

488
00:42:50,276 --> 00:42:54,280
Well, I guess you're here
to throw a tantrum like a baby, huh?

489
00:42:56,616 --> 00:42:59,576
INSPECTION OF FAULTY HELIPAD
CONSTRUCTION IN YEOPOONG-GUN

490
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:03,288
I have evidence that proves
that out of the 20 helipads

491
00:43:03,289 --> 00:43:05,749
renovated in Yeopoong-gun,
17 had faulty lighting.

492
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:08,668
Even on the night of the accident
at the Pyeondongdo helipad,

493
00:43:08,669 --> 00:43:11,172
the lights weren't working properly.

494
00:43:13,508 --> 00:43:19,429
So it wasn't a misdiagnosis,
but the helipad was the problem?

495
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:22,474
I mean, why should we believe
the words of a PH doc

496
00:43:22,475 --> 00:43:25,060
who's taking psychiatric medicine?

497
00:43:25,061 --> 00:43:28,064
Regardless of that fact
and the possibility of misdiagnosis,

498
00:43:28,689 --> 00:43:30,983
the helicopter should've landed safely.

499
00:43:33,861 --> 00:43:37,280
A proper system is what saves lives
in medically underserved regions,

500
00:43:37,281 --> 00:43:40,118
not a skilled doctor.

501
00:43:41,452 --> 00:43:44,747
A system that gets patients
the care they need as soon as possible.

502
00:43:48,876 --> 00:43:53,881
What killed that pilot
was Yeopoong-gun's shitty system.

503
00:43:56,217 --> 00:43:59,302
The hell did you say? "Shitty system"?

504
00:43:59,303 --> 00:44:02,431
Apologize to the family
of the crash victim right this instant.

505
00:44:04,392 --> 00:44:06,936
The only reason I'm giving you
a chance to fix this

506
00:44:07,979 --> 00:44:09,647
is because I also believe

507
00:44:11,399 --> 00:44:13,817
that system could save lives.

508
00:44:13,818 --> 00:44:19,615
YEOPOONG-GUN
HEALTHCARE MODERNIZATION

509
00:44:25,580 --> 00:44:26,956
Dr. Do Jiui!

510
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:37,008
Do you really think
you can bring about change?

511
00:44:39,886 --> 00:44:43,890
The more you provoke the governor,
the worse things will get for you.

512
00:44:47,310 --> 00:44:49,604
PH docs are civil servants

513
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:54,442
which gives the governor the power
to discipline and penalize them at will.

514
00:44:58,529 --> 00:44:59,739
PH docs…

515
00:45:03,451 --> 00:45:04,785
…are also doctors.

516
00:45:08,289 --> 00:45:09,790
Even when the odds are against us…

517
00:45:12,627 --> 00:45:14,420
we have a duty to save lives.

518
00:45:37,902 --> 00:45:39,194
Here.

519
00:45:41,072 --> 00:45:44,575
-  That looks amazing.
-  And it's perfectly seasoned.

520
00:45:45,785 --> 00:45:50,163
So you're saying you don't have
to leave anymore, Dr. Do?

521
00:45:50,164 --> 00:45:52,749
That you'll be here for the full year?

522
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:55,460
Geez, stop asking him that.

523
00:45:55,461 --> 00:45:57,879
He said it hasn't been settled yet.

524
00:45:57,880 --> 00:46:00,131
No, I'll make it so.

525
00:46:00,132 --> 00:46:01,466
Oh, right.

526
00:46:01,467 --> 00:46:04,803
That's great news,
considering all you've been through!

527
00:46:04,804 --> 00:46:06,805
I know, right?

528
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:09,975
We were worried sick that he might
get dragged off to active duty.

529
00:46:11,644 --> 00:46:12,687
Thank you.

530
00:46:14,855 --> 00:46:17,732
About that medication I'm on--

531
00:46:17,733 --> 00:46:20,652
No. You don't owe us an explanation.

532
00:46:20,653 --> 00:46:23,655
Everyone's on some kind of medication.

533
00:46:23,656 --> 00:46:25,699
I take twenty pills
a day just to keep going!

534
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:26,783
Exactly.

535
00:46:26,784 --> 00:46:29,077
If taking medicine is a crime,

536
00:46:29,078 --> 00:46:31,830
then everyone in this room
is serving a life sentence.

537
00:46:31,831 --> 00:46:35,334
That's true,
a life sentence.

538
00:46:37,295 --> 00:46:38,879
Goodness, hurry and eat now.

539
00:46:42,008 --> 00:46:45,720
He's more of a softie
than you might think.

540
00:46:49,098 --> 00:46:53,936
Keep crying like that,
and you're gonna make me cry too.

541
00:46:56,397 --> 00:46:59,108
DAILECTIN - FOR NAUSEA
AND VOMITING OF PREGNANCY

542
00:47:15,207 --> 00:47:16,250
Oh, my…

543
00:47:21,881 --> 00:47:23,757
How are your eyes?

544
00:47:23,758 --> 00:47:27,011
Well, you know…

545
00:47:30,765 --> 00:47:33,391
I wanted to ask you something.

546
00:47:33,392 --> 00:47:35,144
Yes?

547
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:39,482
How did you muster
that kind of courage? Hmm?

548
00:47:40,232 --> 00:47:43,234
If it hadn't turned out
to be appendicitis,

549
00:47:43,235 --> 00:47:45,863
you really would have lost your license.

550
00:47:47,907 --> 00:47:49,867
Um…

551
00:47:50,451 --> 00:47:53,371
Well, we had to save him first…

552
00:47:55,289 --> 00:47:57,707
before we could worry
about what happens next.

553
00:48:01,796 --> 00:48:05,549
Besides, I had known it all along.

554
00:48:07,551 --> 00:48:08,636
Known what?

555
00:48:10,513 --> 00:48:13,014
I knew the people here
wouldn't turn their backs on me,

556
00:48:13,015 --> 00:48:15,434
no matter what happened.

557
00:48:19,647 --> 00:48:22,191
Of course not!

558
00:48:23,025 --> 00:48:24,110
Of course not.

559
00:48:24,944 --> 00:48:26,486
Dr. Do!

560
00:48:26,487 --> 00:48:29,364
What are you doing? Come here for a drink!

561
00:48:29,365 --> 00:48:30,990
Yes, I'm coming.

562
00:48:30,991 --> 00:48:34,452
Where are you?

563
00:48:34,453 --> 00:48:36,371
What are you doing here? Get back in here.

564
00:48:36,372 --> 00:48:39,040
- I said I'm coming.
- Don't make him drink too much.

565
00:48:39,041 --> 00:48:42,544
- Hey, come here.
- Sit.

566
00:48:42,545 --> 00:48:45,463
-  Go easy on him!
-  You're all dead meat today!

567
00:48:45,464 --> 00:48:46,714
Yeah, right.

568
00:48:46,715 --> 00:48:48,258
- Bring us more booze!
- All right.

569
00:48:48,259 --> 00:48:51,094
It's a drink-off then, okay?

570
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:08,654
Hey, honey.

571
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:14,952
I need you to come
to the hospital with me on Monday.

572
00:49:19,248 --> 00:49:22,168
I think I'm a little sick.

573
00:49:39,477 --> 00:49:41,020
Are you leaving now?

574
00:49:44,565 --> 00:49:45,566
Yeah.

575
00:49:52,448 --> 00:49:56,076
I never thought we'd stand before
the ocean together like this again.

576
00:49:59,288 --> 00:50:01,707
I thought it would never happen again.

577
00:50:13,928 --> 00:50:15,304
Jiui.

578
00:50:19,058 --> 00:50:21,393
When I walked out on you back then…

579
00:50:23,437 --> 00:50:25,606
I didn't do it
because I blamed you for it.

580
00:50:28,817 --> 00:50:30,401
I felt like if we stayed together…

581
00:50:32,112 --> 00:50:34,281
…we'd just end up resenting each other.

582
00:50:37,117 --> 00:50:38,536
But…

583
00:50:42,540 --> 00:50:45,084
since I've been here,
I couldn't help but think…

584
00:50:47,002 --> 00:50:50,464
"Would things have been more bearable
if we had stayed together?"

585
00:50:58,681 --> 00:51:00,683
You weren't the only one
who walked out on me.

586
00:51:03,227 --> 00:51:05,187
I did the same thing.

587
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:13,195
I ran away from everything
that reminded me of Seonu…

588
00:51:16,115 --> 00:51:18,659
constantly blaming myself
for failing to save him.

589
00:51:21,704 --> 00:51:22,788
But…

590
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:28,877
don't you think things might have
turned out a little differently…

591
00:51:30,713 --> 00:51:32,423
if someone had helped us out back then?

592
00:51:35,718 --> 00:51:36,719
If only we had…

593
00:51:39,513 --> 00:51:42,182
gotten to the hospital a little sooner.

594
00:51:44,935 --> 00:51:46,312
If only…

595
00:51:48,897 --> 00:51:51,275
Seonu had gotten proper treatment sooner.

596
00:51:54,570 --> 00:51:56,030
Don't you think things might have…

597
00:51:58,282 --> 00:52:00,492
turned out a little differently
for Seonu and us?

598
00:52:10,753 --> 00:52:11,837
Hwayeong.

599
00:52:20,179 --> 00:52:21,639
Why don't we…

600
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:27,019
forgive ourselves now?

601
00:52:32,066 --> 00:52:33,901
We tried our best back then.

602
00:52:54,213 --> 00:52:55,339
What about you?

603
00:52:58,634 --> 00:53:00,928
Have you forgiven yourself?

604
00:53:17,903 --> 00:53:20,155
We should find happiness now.

605
00:53:46,265 --> 00:53:47,474
I'm sorry.

606
00:54:23,343 --> 00:54:25,012
What brings you here?

607
00:54:27,389 --> 00:54:28,974
Do you have anything to tell me?

608
00:54:31,602 --> 00:54:33,020
What are you talking about?

609
00:54:34,354 --> 00:54:36,273
I'm asking if you have
something to tell me.

610
00:54:37,608 --> 00:54:39,902
Stop talking in riddles.

611
00:54:46,658 --> 00:54:48,784
You're pregnant.

612
00:54:51,872 --> 00:54:55,541
Was the reason
you haven't been feeling well recently

613
00:54:55,542 --> 00:54:57,044
because you're pregnant?

614
00:54:59,463 --> 00:55:01,506
When you suddenly took a day off,

615
00:55:01,507 --> 00:55:04,885
did you go to the hospital alone
without telling me?

616
00:55:08,138 --> 00:55:09,139
I did.

617
00:55:12,726 --> 00:55:15,938
And you had no intention
of ever telling me, right?

618
00:55:17,105 --> 00:55:18,106
Right?

619
00:55:20,359 --> 00:55:23,819
Say something!

620
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:25,739
Why did you do that?

621
00:55:28,784 --> 00:55:32,287
It's because
I haven't made a decision yet.

622
00:55:35,624 --> 00:55:38,376
You're only here temporarily, Dr. Yong.

623
00:55:38,377 --> 00:55:42,797
You may feel like you're really into me,
but your world is back in Seoul,

624
00:55:42,798 --> 00:55:45,424
at a high-end clinic
on Baeng Baeng Intersection

625
00:55:45,425 --> 00:55:47,802
where you'd be a big-shot doctor
of Korean medicine.

626
00:55:47,803 --> 00:55:51,681
And my world is this tiny, dusty village.

627
00:55:51,682 --> 00:55:55,477
I don't think people like us can coexist
in the same space for too long.

628
00:55:59,189 --> 00:56:01,692
Is that why you weren't
ever going to tell me?

629
00:56:05,279 --> 00:56:07,154
Do you really have so little faith in me?

630
00:56:07,155 --> 00:56:09,283
This isn't about you.

631
00:56:10,826 --> 00:56:12,953
I don't have any faith in myself.

632
00:56:15,497 --> 00:56:16,915
Ms. Eom.

633
00:56:18,333 --> 00:56:21,378
This is just the way I am…

634
00:56:24,464 --> 00:56:26,675
so don't waste your time
worrying about me.

635
00:56:29,678 --> 00:56:31,430
I'm going to do things my way.

636
00:56:57,289 --> 00:56:59,207
Here, try some.

637
00:57:00,083 --> 00:57:01,251
- Is it good?
- Yeah!

638
00:57:13,096 --> 00:57:15,014
It's good, isn't it?

639
00:57:20,771 --> 00:57:22,189
I love this.

640
00:57:23,315 --> 00:57:24,940
What do you mean?

641
00:57:24,941 --> 00:57:27,611
Having you here.

642
00:57:34,284 --> 00:57:35,327
So…

643
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:42,709
I'm going to go see Seonu tomorrow.

644
00:57:44,294 --> 00:57:46,088
Because I haven't said goodbye yet.

645
00:57:46,922 --> 00:57:48,173
Oh…

646
00:57:48,882 --> 00:57:52,302
Can you come with me?

647
00:57:56,181 --> 00:58:00,519
I feel like I'll be able to go
if you come with me.

648
00:59:05,500 --> 00:59:09,837
KIM SEONU

649
00:59:09,838 --> 00:59:12,173
IN MEMORY OF OUR FRIEND,
KIM SEONU,

650
00:59:12,174 --> 00:59:14,091
WHO WOULD HAVE MADE
AN AMAZING DOCTOR

651
00:59:14,092 --> 00:59:18,221
HANGUK UNIVERSITY
MEDICAL SCHOOL CLASS OF 2014

652
00:59:37,073 --> 00:59:38,116
Seonu.

653
00:59:46,750 --> 00:59:48,418
Seonu, I'm sorry.

654
00:59:55,634 --> 00:59:57,552
I'm sorry I kept you waiting so long.

655
01:00:54,317 --> 01:00:55,986
Thank you…

656
01:00:59,865 --> 01:01:01,700
for coming to see Seonu with me today.

657
01:01:03,869 --> 01:01:08,164
Thank you for staying with me.

658
01:01:12,502 --> 01:01:15,881
I think
this is where I first met you.

659
01:01:17,465 --> 01:01:19,926
What was that like?
Did you think I was cute?

660
01:01:21,845 --> 01:01:23,345
Hmm…

661
01:01:23,346 --> 01:01:24,472
You were a little scary.

662
01:01:25,348 --> 01:01:27,600
What the heck?

663
01:01:27,601 --> 01:01:28,602
Seriously?

664
01:01:29,519 --> 01:01:34,941
They say there are three things a PH doc
must avoid on an island, you see.

665
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:37,861
Three things? What are they?

666
01:01:38,778 --> 01:01:40,988
They say if you don't avoid
those three things,

667
01:01:40,989 --> 01:01:42,949
you'll never leave an island.

668
01:01:45,869 --> 01:01:47,203
Incidents…

669
01:01:50,999 --> 01:01:54,461
people, and…

670
01:01:56,421 --> 01:01:57,464
love.

671
01:02:08,099 --> 01:02:09,809
I think I knew back then…

672
01:02:11,811 --> 01:02:14,229
that I was never going to leave.

673
01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:07,534
ON OFFICIAL DUTY

674
01:03:27,345 --> 01:03:30,724
YEOPOONG-GUN

675
01:03:35,020 --> 01:03:37,438
We're with the Yeopoong-gun
Audit Department.

676
01:03:37,439 --> 01:03:40,650
Stop what you're doing
and cooperate with our investigation.

677
01:03:42,110 --> 01:03:45,154
Dr. Jiui! This is bad!

678
01:03:45,155 --> 01:03:49,117
You need to come down
to the center right now!

679
01:03:53,705 --> 01:03:54,913
DO NOT APPROACH

680
01:03:54,914 --> 01:03:59,001
Those are patient records.
You're not supposed to touch those.

681
01:03:59,002 --> 01:04:01,378
Excuse me!

682
01:04:01,379 --> 01:04:02,838
Keep going.

683
01:04:02,839 --> 01:04:04,466
What do you think you're doing?

684
01:04:05,592 --> 01:04:08,761
We have reason to believe this center
is involved in a kickback scheme.

685
01:04:08,762 --> 01:04:10,722
Kickbacks? What are you talking about?

686
01:04:11,347 --> 01:04:14,475
A recent internal audit uncovered evidence
that this clinic accepted

687
01:04:14,476 --> 01:04:17,853
kickbacks from Manu Pharmaceuticals
in exchange for procuring its drugs.

688
01:04:17,854 --> 01:04:19,897
An investigation is currently underway.

689
01:04:19,898 --> 01:04:22,649
As a result, operations
at the Pyeondong Health Center

690
01:04:22,650 --> 01:04:25,152
will be suspended until
the investigation is concluded.

691
01:04:25,153 --> 01:04:26,613
You're suspending our operations?

692
01:04:36,372 --> 01:04:37,956
Hello?

693
01:04:37,957 --> 01:04:39,792
Hey, Dr. Do Jiui.

694
01:04:39,793 --> 01:04:44,379
I wonder if you received my response yet.

695
01:04:44,380 --> 01:04:50,762
I hope you enjoy a little taste
of that shitty system you mentioned.

696
01:04:51,513 --> 01:04:54,598
The system that teaches
a lowly civil servant

697
01:04:54,599 --> 01:04:57,142
not to mess with the governor, got it?

698
01:04:57,143 --> 01:05:03,191
The kind of system that shows a guard dog
what happens when it barks at its master!

699
01:05:04,484 --> 01:05:06,069
Better get in line.

700
01:05:08,530 --> 01:05:10,448
Punk-ass bastard.

701
01:05:18,414 --> 01:05:20,750
Ko Changmok, that son of a bitch.

702
01:05:35,682 --> 01:05:38,517
THAT PROMISE YOU MADE
TO YOURSELF

703
01:05:38,518 --> 01:05:42,229
TO NEVER BE HAPPY AGAIN…

704
01:05:42,230 --> 01:05:46,067
DON'T KEEP IT.

705
01:05:54,325 --> 01:05:57,537
THE BEST KIND OF RAMYEON
IS THE KIND I'M SHARING WITH YOU

706
01:05:58,121 --> 01:06:01,541
SOMEONE ON MY SIDE?

707
01:06:06,546 --> 01:06:09,549
HARI AND I ARE THE SAME AGE

708
01:06:13,636 --> 01:06:16,556
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

709
01:06:17,182 --> 01:06:18,807
We'll be transferring soon.

710
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:21,185
It's about time
you returned to your place.

711
01:06:21,186 --> 01:06:23,562
I have something to tell you,
Dr. Do.

712
01:06:24,898 --> 01:06:26,148
Hey!

713
01:06:26,149 --> 01:06:28,901
If any of you touch
a single thing here, it's theft.

714
01:06:28,902 --> 01:06:31,278
I don't think the center
should be shut down,

715
01:06:31,279 --> 01:06:33,655
which is why I've come up with a solution.

716
01:06:33,656 --> 01:06:36,033
I'd say this is a no-brainer.

717
01:06:36,034 --> 01:06:38,535
I'm the one who stole this, so…

718
01:06:38,536 --> 01:06:40,829
Something terrible will happen
if you keep this up!

719
01:06:40,830 --> 01:06:43,041
I'm going to keep
fighting until the end.

720
01:06:46,920 --> 01:06:48,922
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park
